ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Deep Phenotyping Site ID
Notes: In person session site ID

ElementDescription: Dark Enhanced Startle (DES) version
Notes: 1= Dark First; 2 = Light First

ElementDescription: Baseline startle magnitude
Notes: Measured in microvolts

ElementDescription: Dark Enhanced Startle: dark-enhanced startle percent potentiation block1
Notes: Measured in percentage during dark enhanced startle

ElementDescription: Acquisition: fear-potentiated startle percent potentiation threat signal
Notes: Measured in percentage during acquisition phase

ElementDescription: Acquisition: fear-potentiated startle percent potentiation safety signal
Notes: Measured in percentage during acquisition phase

ElementDescription: Extinction: fear-potentiated startle percent potentiation to threat, early (bl1)
Notes: Measured in percentage during extinction phase

ElementDescription: Extinction: fear-potentiated startle percent potentiation to threat, late (bl4)
Notes: Measured in percentage during extinction phase

ElementDescription: Baseline skin conductance level
Notes: Measured in microsiemens

ElementDescription: Acquisition: skin conductance response threat signal
Notes: Measured in microsiemens during acquisition phase

ElementDescription: Acquisition: skin conductance response safety signal
Notes: Measured in microsiemens during acquisition phase

ElementDescription: Extinction: skin conductance response to threat, early (bl1)
Notes: Measured in microsiemens during extinction phase

ElementDescription: Extinction: skin conductance response to threat, late (bl4)
Notes: Measured in microsiemens during extinction phase

ElementDescription: Baseline heart rate
Notes: Measured in beats per minute (BPM) at rest

ElementDescription: Dark Enhanced Startle: average heart rate during dark
Notes: Mean Heart rate measured in beats per minute (BPM) during dark enhanced startle

ElementDescription: Acquisition: average heart rate during acquisition
Notes: Mean Heart rate measured in beats per minute (BPM) during acquisition phase

ElementDescription: Extinction: average heart rate during extinction
Notes: Mean Heart rate measured in beats per minute (BPM) during extinction phase

ElementDescription: Respiratory sinus arrythmia (RSA) at rest
Notes: Average RSA (frequency domain estimate)  during Rest

ElementDescription: Average Respiratory sinus arrythmia in dark
Notes: Average RSA (frequency domain estimate) in dark

ElementDescription: Average Respiratory sinus arrythmia during acquisition
Notes: Average RSA (frequency domain estimate) during acquisition

ElementDescription: Average Respiratory sinus arrythmia during extinction
Notes: Average RSA (frequency domain estimate) during extinction
